具体算法

training


训练过程理论上是逐步加噪使图像成为一个高斯噪声，实际上随机选择步数t，从原图直接加噪

generating


生成时不直接取概率最大的点，而是加一个采样的随机性，这样效果更好。

数学推导

极大似然

生成模型本质上是要找到一个映射使得的分布与数据集尽可能接近。
可以证明，最大化样本的极大似然等价于最小化两个分布的KL散度。
$$
\begin{align*}
\theta^* &= \arg\max_\theta \prod_{i=1}^{m} P_\theta(x_i) \
&= \arg\max_\theta \sum_{i=1}^m \log P_\theta(x_i) \
&\approx \arg\max_{\theta} \mathbb{E}{x\sim P{data}} [\log P_\theta(x)] \
&= \arg\max_\theta \int_x P_\theta(x)\log P_\theta(x) dx - \int_x P_{data}(x)\log P_{data}(x) dx \
&= \arg\max_\theta \int_x P_{data}(x)\log \frac{P_\theta(x)}{P_{data}(x)} dx \
&= \arg\min_\theta KL(P_{data}||P_\theta)
\end{align*}
$$

DDPM

DDPM从一个纯高斯分布逐渐去噪还原出图像
$P_\theta(x_{t-1}|x_t)\propto exp(-||G(x_t)-x_{t-1}||2)P{\theta}(x_0) = \int_{x_1:x_T}^{}P(x_T)P_{\theta}(x_{T-1}|x_T)\dots P_{\theta}(x_{t-1}|x_t)\dots P_{\theta}(x_0|x_1)dx_1:x_Tq(x_1:x_T|x_0)=q(x_1|x_0)q(x_2|x_1)\dots q(x_T|x_{T-1})$

类似于VAE的推导，我们可以推导出的lower bound。

  • diffusion: Maximize Maximize

为了Maximize ，进行推导：

得到
第二项没有参数可优化。因为第三项是求和，在优化目标中占主要部分，考虑最大化最后一项:


得到 $$q(x_{t-1}|x_t, x_0)\sim N(\frac{\sqrt{\bar{\alpha}{t-1}}\beta_tx_0+\sqrt{\bar{\alpha}t}(1-\bar{\alpha}{t-1})x_t}{1-\bar{\alpha}t},\frac{1-\bar{\alpha}{t-1}}{1-\bar{\alpha}{t}}\beta_tI)$$

则有了

又因为

$$
\begin{align}
&\mu_q(x_t, x_0) = \frac{\sqrt{\alpha_t}(1 - \bar{\alpha}{t-1})x_t + \sqrt{\bar{\alpha}{t-1}}(1 - \alpha_t)x_0}{1 - \bar{\alpha}t}\
&\mu{\theta}(x_t, t) = \frac{\sqrt{\alpha_t}(1 - \bar{\alpha}{t-1})x_t + \sqrt{\bar{\alpha}{t-1}}(1 - \alpha_t)\hat{x_{\theta}}(x_t,t)}{1 - \bar{\alpha}_t}\
\end{align}
$$

所以

$$
\begin{align}
&\arg \min_\theta D_{\mathrm{KL}}(q(x_{t-1}|x_t, x_0) || p_\theta(x_{t-1}|x_t)) \
=& \arg \min_\theta \frac{1}{2\sigma_q^2(t)} |\mu_\theta - \mu_q|^2_2 \
=& \arg \min_\theta \frac{1}{2\sigma_q^2(t)} \frac{\bar{\alpha}_{t-1}(1 - \alpha_t)^2}{(1 - \bar{\alpha}t)^2} |\hat{x}{\theta}(x_t, t) - x_0|^2
\end{align}
$$

这里假定了两个分布的方差相等

又或者考虑预测噪声

$$
\begin{align}
&\mu_q(x_t,x_0)= \frac{1}{\sqrt{\alpha_t}} x_t - \frac{1 - \alpha_t}{\sqrt{\alpha_t}\sqrt{1-\bar{\alpha}t}} \epsilon_0\
&\mu{\theta}(x_t,t)= \frac{1}{\sqrt{\alpha_t}} x_t - \frac{1 - \alpha_t}{\sqrt{\alpha_t}\sqrt{1-\bar{\alpha}t}} \hat{\epsilon}{\theta}(x_t,t)
\end{align}
$$

则有

$$
\begin{align}
&\arg \min_\theta D_{\mathrm{KL}}(q(x_{t-1}|x_t, x_0) || p_\theta(x_{t-1}|x_t)) \
=& \arg \min_\theta \frac{1}{2\sigma_q^2(t)} |\mu_0 - \mu_q|^2 \
=& \arg \min_\theta \frac{1}{2\sigma_q^2(t)} \left|\frac{1}{\sqrt{\alpha_t}}x_t - \frac{1 - \alpha_t}{\sqrt{1 - \alpha_t\sqrt{\alpha_t}}}\hat{\epsilon}{\theta}(x_t, t) - \frac{1}{\sqrt{\alpha_t}}x_t + \frac{1 - \alpha_t}{\sqrt{1 - \alpha_t\sqrt{\alpha_t}}}\epsilon_0\right|^2 \
=& \arg \min\theta \frac{1}{2\sigma_q^2(t)} \left|\frac{1 - \alpha_t}{\sqrt{1 - \alpha_t\sqrt{\alpha_t}}}\epsilon_0 - \frac{1 - \alpha_t}{\sqrt{1 - \alpha_t\sqrt{\alpha_t}}}\hat{\epsilon}{\theta}(x_t, t)\right|^2 \
=&\arg \min\theta \frac{1}{2\sigma_q^2(t)} \left|\frac{1 - \alpha_t}{\sqrt{1 - \alpha_t\sqrt{\alpha_t}}}(\epsilon_0 - \hat{\epsilon}{\theta}(x_t, t))\right|^2 \
=& \arg \min\theta \frac{1}{2\sigma_q^2(t)} \frac{(1 - \alpha_t)^2}{(1 - \alpha_t)\alpha_t} |\epsilon_0 - \hat{\epsilon}_{\theta}(x_t, t)|^2
\end{align}
$$

最终的损失函数省略了系数，只保留了MSE形式
